  "tables": [
    {
      "block_id": "1ce4750c-f3ba-8047-a59d-e435d383c3fd",
      "heading": "Summary Table KT",
      "rows": [
        [
          "Task",
          "Context",
          "Student Performance Definition",
          "Target",
          "Students",
          "Courses",
          "Data sources",
          "Features",
          "Flaw of Previous Models",
          "Novelty of Model",
          "Preprocessing Details",
          "Models",
          "Assessment Strategy",
          "Performance Metric: Best Model",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Higher Education",
          "Predict Presented Code Solution",
          "Code Submission",
          "246 students",
          "1 Computer Science Course",
          "Open Ended Questions, Code Submissions",
          "[Student Knowledge State]",
          "Most KT models only analyze and predict binary-valued learner responses to questions → making it difficult to use for open-ended questions.",
          "OKT presents a framework that is able to model and predict knowledge from open-ended questions.\n\n",
          "The model creates a continuous embedding representation to encodde the open-ended answers. \n\nKnowledge updates follow the same logic as other KT models.\n\nStudent is represented, for each timestep, as a triple: question-answer-correctedness.\n\nEmbedding of questions is done by GPT-2 and answers are of ASTNN.\n\nThe knowledge state of the student is updated by a LSTM AND is the input of the code generation.\n",
          "OKT-DKT, OKT-AKT, OKT-DKVMN",
          "Holdout Method",
          "{CodeBLEU: 0.565 - OKT-AKT, Dist-1: 0.396 - OKT-AKT, Test Loss: 0.133 - OKT-AKT}",
          "OKT does not measure wether the answer is correct or not. It predicts the learners’ open ended answer → which could later be tested for correctedness. Since this is not a common task in KT, ther are no baselines to compare against. To address that the authors test multiple variants of OKT: using other frameworks for knowledge update.",
          "Does not address the standard KT task of predicting correctedness.\n\nLimited number of explored Generative Moddels for Code Generation.\n\nSmall dataset."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
  ],
