    {
      "id": "1944750c-f3ba-80c6-ac7a-e600aed2206c",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "One of the problems with KT is that they treat answers as correct/incorrect. While valuable, this information is somewhat incomplete and likely could be complemented if questions were “open-ended,” - especially when the goal is to create a model of learner’s knowledge. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "1944750c-f3ba-80c6-ac7a-e600aed2206c",
        "parent": {
          "type": "page_id",
          "page_id": "18c4750c-f3ba-80de-83bf-d970b7615174"
        },
        "created_time": "2025-02-08T23:59:00.000Z",
        "last_edited_time": "2025-02-09T00:09:00.000Z",
